definition.value: A cell of a hematopoietic lineage.

label.value: CD8-positive, CXCR3-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell

definition.value: A CD8-positive alpha-beta-positive T cell with the phenotype CXCR3-positive and having suppressor function. They are capable of producing IL-10, suppressing proliferation, and suppressing IFN-gamma production.
These cells may be the human equivalent of murine CD8-positive, CD122-positive alpha-beta regulatory T cell. They are also found in the CD45RA-negative and CD62L-positive fraction.
CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that produces IL-22.
TH22 cells are also reportedly CCR4-positive, CCR6-positive, CCR10-positive, CXCR3-negative. TH22 cells are reportedly capable of secreting IL-13.

label.value: activated CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell, human

definition.value: A recently activated CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, CD38-positive, CD69-positive, CD62L-negative, CD127-negative, and CD25-positive.

This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'activated CD4+ T cell', but includes via logical inference from its parent additional markers known to be expressed on activated CD4+ T cells.  The inclusion of HLA-DRA in the definition restricts this definition to human activated CD4+ T cells, as activated mouse T cells do not express MHC class II.
A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD45RA-positive.
A naive regulatory T cell with the phenotype CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CD127lo, CCR4-positive, and CD45RO-negative.
This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'naive CCR4+ Treg'.  The definition is valid for human; its applicability for mouse and other species is unknown.
A memory regulatory T cell with phenotype CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CD127lo, CCR4-positive, and CD45RO-positive.
This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'memory CCR4+ Treg'.  The definition is valid for human; its applicability for mouse and other species is unknown.

label.value: CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CCR4-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell

definition.value: A CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell with the additional phenotype CCR4-positive.
This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'CCR4+ Treg'.  The definition is valid for human; its applicability for mouse and other species is unknown.

label.value: activated CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CCR4-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell, human

definition.value: A CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CCR4-positive, alpha-beta T regulatory cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, indicating recent activation.

This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'activated CCR4+ Treg'.  The inclusion of HLA-DRA in the definition restricts this definition to human activated CD4+ T cells, as activated mouse T cells do not express MHC class II.

label.value: activated CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell, human

definition.value: A recently activated CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, CD38-positive, CD69-positive, CD62L-negative, CD127-negative, CCR7-negative, and CD25-positive.

This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'activated CD8+ T cell', but includes via logical inference from its parent additional markers known to be expressed on activated CD8+ T cells.  The inclusion of HLA-DRA in the definition restricts this definition to human activated CD8+ T cells, as activated mouse T cells do not express MHC class II.
A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD45RA-positive.

This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'effector CD8+ T cell'.  The functional characteristics of this cell type currently undefined in CL, which affects its proper placement within the hierarchy.

label.value: CD4-positive, CXCR3-negative, CCR6-negative, alpha-beta T cell

definition.value: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has the phenotype CXCR3-negative, CCR6-negative.
This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'non-Th1/Th17 CD4+ T cell'.  Cells of this phenotype may include T-helper 2 T cells and some naive CD4+ T cells.

label.value: CD8-positive, CXCR3-negative, CCR6-negative, alpha-beta T cell

definition.value: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has the phenotype CXCR3-negative, CCR6-negative.
This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'non-Tc1/Tc17 CD8+ T cell'.  Cells of this phenotype may include Tc2 T cells and some naive CD8+ T cells.
A memory B cell that lacks expression of surface IgD.
This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'IgD- memory B cell'.  The majority of these cells are class-switched, though some are IgM-positive.

label.value: effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell, terminally differentiated

definition.value: A CD8-positive, alpha beta memory T cell with the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CD45RO-negative, and CCR7-negative.
This cell type is seen human but not found in the mouse.
An enucleate erythrocyte that is GlyA-positive.
Marker is associated with human cell types.
An enucleate erythrocyte that is Lyg-76-high.
Marker is associated with mouse cell types.

label.value: CD2-positive, CD5-positive, CD44-positive alpha-beta intraepithelial T cell

definition.value: Intraepithelial T cells with a memory phenotype of CD2-positive, CD5-positive, and CD44-positive.

A CD4-positive, CXCR5-positive, CCR7-negative alpha-beta T cell located in follicles of secondary lymph nodes that expresses is BCL6-high, ICOS-high and PD1-high, and stimulates follicular B cells to undergo class-switching and antibody production.

label.value: immature NK T cell stage I

definition.value: A CD24-high, CD4-low, CD8-low, CD44-negative, NK1.1-negative NK T cell.

label.value: immature NK T cell stage II

definition.value: A CD24-low, CD44-negative, NK1.1-negative NK T cell.
NKT.44-NK1.1-.Th was assigned as an exact synonym based on sorting strategy displayed at immgene.org.

label.value: immature NK T cell stage III

definition.value: A CD24-low, CD44-positive, DX5-low, NK1.1-negative NK T cell.

label.value: immature NK T cell stage IV

definition.value: A CD24-low, CD44-positive, DX5-high, NK1.1-negative NK T cell.
A precursor B cell that is CD45RA-positive, CD43-positive, CD24-positive and BP-1-negative.
Markers are commonly associated with mouse cells. These cells are also reportedly RAG1-positive and RAG2-positive.
A pre-B cell precursor is CD19-low, CD22-positive , CD34-positive, CD38-positive.
Late pro-B cells are also reportedly CD10-positive, CD20-negative, CD21-negative, and TdT-positive. Transcription factors: PU.1-positive, Ikaros-positive, E2A-positive, and PAX5-positive.

A precursor B cell is CD45R-positive, CD43-positive, CD24-positive, and BP-positive. Intracellularly expression of surrogate light chain, Rag1 and Rag2, TdT, occurs while there is no expression of mu heavy chain.
A pre-BCR-positive precursor B cell that is CD24-high, CD25-positive, CD43-positive, CD45R-positive and BP-positive.
A pre-BCR positive T cell that is CD38-high.
Markers are associated with human cells.

A pre-B cell that is pre-BCR-negative, and the kappa- and lambda- light immunoglobulin light chain-negative, CD43-low, and is BP-1-positive, CD45R-positive and CD25-positive. This cell type is also described as being AA4-positive, IgM-negative, CD19-positive, CD43-low/negative, and HSA-positive.
Fraction D precursor B cells are also reportedly CD24-positive and sIgD-negative.
A small pre-B cell that is CD22-positive and CD38-low.
Markers are associated with human cell. RAG expression maybe diminishing.

An immature B cell that is IgM-positive, CD45R-positive, CD43-low, CD25-negative, and CD127-negative. This cell type has also been described as being AA4-positive, IgM-positive, CD19-positive, CD43-low/negative, and HSA-positive.
Markers associated with mouse cells. These cells are also reportedly sIgD-negative.
An immature B cell that is CD38-negative, CD10-low, CD21-low, and CD22-high.
Markers are associated with human cell type.

A mature B cell subset originally defined as having being CD45R-positive, IgM-positive, IgD-positive and CD43-negative. Subsequent research demonstrated being CD21-positive and CD23-negative and CD93 negative.

A T-helper cell that is characterized by secreting interleukin 9 and responding to helminth infections. This cell-type can derives from Th2 cells in the presence of TGF-beta and IL-4. Th2 cytokine production is surpressed.

A CD38-positive naive B cell is a mature B cell that has the phenotype CD38-positive, surface IgD-positive, surface IgM-positive, and CD27-negative, and that has not yet been activated by antigen in the periphery.

A CD38-negative naive B cell is a mature B cell that has the phenotype CD38-negative, surface IgD-positive, surface IgM-positive, and CD27-negative, that has not yet been activated by antigen in the periphery.

label.value: IgG-positive double negative memory B cell

definition.value: An IgG-positive double negative memory B cell is a double negative memory B cell with the phenotype IgG-positive, IgD-negative, and CD27-negative.

label.value: IgG-negative double negative memory B cell

definition.value: An IgG-negative double negative memory B cell is a double negative memory B cell with the phenotype IgG-negative, IgD-negative, and CD27-negative.
A CD38-positive IgG memory B cell is a class switched memory B cell that expresses IgG on the cell surface with the phenotype CD38-positive and IgG-positive.

label.value: IgD-positive CD38-positive IgG memory B cell

definition.value: An IgD-positive CD38-positive IgG memory B cell is a CD38-positive IgG-positive class switched memory B cell that has class switched and expresses IgD on the cell surface with the phenotype IgD-positive, CD38-positive, and IgG-positive.

label.value: IgD-negative CD38-positive IgG memory B cell

definition.value: An IgD-negative CD38-positive IgG memory B cell is a CD38-positive IgG-positive that has class switched and lacks expression of IgD on the cell surface with the phenotype IgD-negative, CD38-positive, and IgG-positive.

A CD38-negative IgG memory B cell is a IgG-positive class switched memory B cell that has class switched and expresses IgG on the cell surface with the phenotype CD38-negative, IgD-negative, and IgG-positive.

A B220-positive CD38-positive naive B cell is a CD38-positive naive B cell that has the phenotype B220-positive, CD38-positive, surface IgD-positive, surface IgM-positive, and CD27-negative, and that has not yet been activated by antigen in the periphery.

A B220-low CD38-positive naive B cell is a CD38-positive naive B cell that has the phenotype B220-low, CD38-positive, surface IgD-positive, surface IgM-positive, and CD27-negative, that has not yet been activated by antigen in the periphery.
An CD38-negative unswitched memory B cell is an unswitched memory B cell that has the phenotype CD38-negative, IgD-positive, CD138-negative, and IgG-negative.

label.value: B220-positive CD38-negative unswitched memory B cell

definition.value: A B220-positive CD38-negative unswitched memory B cell is a CD38-negative unswitched memory B cell that has the phenotype B220-positive, CD38-negative, IgD-positive, CD138-negative, and IgG-negative.

label.value: B220-low CD38-negative unswitched memory B cell

definition.value: A B220-low CD38-negative unswitched memory B cell is a CD38-negative unswitched memory B cell that has the phenotype B220-low, CD38-negative, IgD-positive, CD138-negative, and IgG-negative.
A CD38-positive unswitched memory B cell is an unswitched memory B cell that has the phenotype CD38-positive, IgD-positive, CD138-negative, and IgG-negative.

label.value: B220-positive CD38-positive unswitched memory B cell

definition.value: A B220-positive CD38-positive unswitched memory B cell is a CD38-positive unswitched memory B cell that has the phenotype B220-positive, CD38-positive, IgD-positive, CD138-negative, and IgG-negative.

label.value: B220-low CD38-positive unswitched memory B cell

definition.value: A B220-low CD38-positive unswitched memory B cell is a CD38-positive unswitched memory B cell that has the phenotype B220-low, CD38-positive, IgD-positive, CD138-negative, and IgG-negative.
